23 Eylรผl 2019 tarihinde unipa sisteminden (sis.altinbas.edu.tr) รถฤrencilerimizin ders seรงimleri olacaktฤฑr.

ders seรงim tarihinden รถnce parola ve ลifresi olmayan รถฤrencilerimizin bu iลlemi tamamlamalarฤฑ gerekmektedir.

Dear Students,

Course selection period begins on September 23, 2019. To select courses, you will have to log into the unipa system (sis.altinbas.edu.tr).
In case you currently do not have a password, you need to have a password before the course selection period begins.  
Otherwise, you will not be able to select courses online.

[23.09.2019 3:39:23 PM] โช+964ย780ย033ย4565โฌ: ear Student,

First of all, I would like to congratulate you for your acceptance to Altฤฑnbaล University and I assure you that we are looking forward to meet with you in our Orientation Week in Mahmutbey Campus between 23-27 September, 2019.

 

As the start of the academic year is approaching, I would like to inform you about the orientation program.

 

Attached, you may find the itinerary for the orientation week. There will be an orientation presentation on Tuesday, 24.09.2019. If you would like to attend, you may kindly come in Fatma Altฤฑnbaล Conference Hall at 13.30.

 

We arranged a city tour for our new students on Friday, 27.09.2019.

 

Also, we arranged a shuttle in order to go to Tax Office on Wednesday, 25.09.2019. We may kindly help you when you get a tax number and when you pay your tax for once. 

 

Please kindly send us an e-mail on international@altinbas.edu.tr if you will be able to join us in the in each of the orientation programs OR you can come to the International Office to sign in. (You need to sign up for each event, and especially for the Istanbul City Tour which will be held on September 27, 2019 at 10:00 am.)

 

We would like to inform you that the city tour is not for free, we have just arranged shuttle services and we may kindly guide the tour.

 

Please note that your participation to the orientation program is very important for you to collect the necessary information that you will need during your studies at Altฤฑnbaล University.

 

You may see also the information package attached in order to see the important details on being a student in Altฤฑnbaล University. Please kindly read it carefully.

 

In the meanwhile, if you have any further questions, please do not hesitate to contact us.

 

Hope to see you soon!

[17.03.2020 5:00:38 PM] โช+964ย771ย232ย3861โฌ: Dear Students,
Tests related to the live narration of the courses connected to your school are planned to be carried out on Wednesday, March 18, 2020 through the Distance Education Center.

1. Firstly Login to Distance Learning Center -Moodle Program from http://uzem.altinbas.edu.tr with your computer login account and password.
2. Search your course under the title of "All Courses" from your Distance Learning Center page and add yourself to the relevant course section.(Example; โDEN101โ) 3. When the lesson starts, you can connect to the live lesson from the "Join Meeting" button from the live lesson link in your Distance Learning Center lesson.

What to do in case of need for support;
โข For help on this subject, you can find the guides under the heading โStudentโ in the top menu on http://uzem.altinbas.edu.tr โข You can get support from uzem@altinbas.edu.tr on Adobe Connect-moodle usage details and technical issues.
โข If you cannot login to Uzem.altinbas.edu.tr, you can get support from destek@altinbas.edu.tr for issues such as account and password. (For password renewal, you can renew your password by entering the necessary information from reset.altinbas.edu.tr address. Information such as date of birth, father name should match with your identity information.)
โข If need further assistance, call the call center 0212 604 01 00 and they will direct you to support people.

Important;
Your or the internet service providers internet speed could be slow nowadays. You might get errors when you are using video connections.
Before asking for support, make sure whether your problem is caused by these issues and check your internet connections.

Best Regards,
